and

public static <T> Filter<T> and(Filter<T>... filters)
Gets a composite filter that implements short-circuiting AND logic. It sends the object to each of the given filters in order, possibly transforming it at each step, then returns the final filter's response. Along the way, if any filter returns null, the remaining filters will be skipped and it will return null.

When the composite filter is closed, the underlying filters will be closed.

Type Parameters:
T - the type.
Parameters:
filters - the filters.
Returns:
the composite filter.

not

public static <T> Filter<T> not(Filter<T> filter)
Gets a filter that inverts the boolean response of the given filter. Objects that return any value when passed to the wrapped filter will return null. Those that return null will instead return the original value.

When the returned filter is closed, the underlying filter will be closed.

Type Parameters:
T - the type.
Parameters:
filter - the filter to invert.
Returns:
the inverting filter.

or

public static <T> Filter<T> or(Filter<T>... filters)
Gets a composite filter that implements short-circuiting OR logic. It sends the original object to each of the given filters in order, until one gives a non-null result, then returns that result. If all filters return null, this filter will also return null.

When the composite filter is closed, the underlying filters will be closed.

Type Parameters:
T - the type.
Parameters:
filters - the filters.
Returns:
the composite filter.
